            Enable <strong>Countdown</strong> for a 10-second lead-in to get in
            position before the first round starts
          </li>
          <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Start</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The beep at the work/rest transition is the defining feature of a good
        Tabata timer. At 10 seconds of rest there is no time to look at the
        screen — the audio cue is what tells you to start again.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">
        2. Classic HIIT intervals
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        "HIIT" covers a wide range of work-to-rest ratios beyond Tabata. The
        protocol is the same — alternate work and rest, repeat for rounds — but
        the ratio shifts the training emphasis:
      </p>
