      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">
        4. EMOM-style HIIT
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Every Minute On the Minute intervals apply HIIT principles in a
        self-regulating format: you work at the start of each minute and
        whatever time remains is your rest. If you complete 15 calories on the
        assault bike in 40 seconds, you get 20 seconds of rest. Move faster,
        recover more.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        EMOM-style HIIT scales automatically by fitness level without changing
        the timer settings. A fitter athlete finishes faster and recovers more.
        A newer athlete finishes slower, works harder, and has less rest — which
        is the appropriate stimulus for their level. This makes EMOM intervals
        well suited to group training and partner workouts.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Common EMOM HIIT setups: 12 calories on the rower every minute for 10
        rounds, 10 kettlebell swings every minute for 12 rounds, 15 wall balls
        every minute for 8 rounds, 5 strict pull-ups every minute for 10
        rounds. The movement should be completable in 30–45 seconds to leave
        meaningful rest.
      </p>
